I have successfully completed the M3 judge-facing investigation experience and browser gate. Below is a summary of the work done:

### 1. Typescript Parity (`packages/contracts`)
* Added strict TypeScript matching for the backend models under [index.ts](file:///D:/Work/Codex/Hackathon%20Projects/OpenAI%20Hackathon/.agent-worktrees/incident-m3-frontend/packages/contracts/src/index.ts), including `InvestigationReport`, `RankedHypothesis`, `CodeMapping`, `SpecialistFinding`, `FalsificationTest`, `AffectedFile`, `EvidenceCitation`, `IncidentSummary`, and `RejectedClaim`.

### 2. Client API Integrations (`apps/web`)
* Exposed the `getIncidentInvestigation` function under [api.ts](file:///D:/Work/Codex/Hackathon%20Projects/OpenAI%20Hackathon/.agent-worktrees/incident-m3-frontend/apps/web/lib/api.ts) to fetch the investigation report from `/api/v1/incidents/{id}/investigation`.
* Added corresponding unit test coverage in [api.test.ts](file:///D:/Work/Codex/Hackathon%20Projects/OpenAI%20Hackathon/.agent-worktrees/incident-m3-frontend/apps/web/lib/api.test.ts).

### 3. Investigation UI Room Component (`apps/web`)
* Updated the details page component at [page.tsx](file:///D:/Work/Codex/Hackathon%20Projects/OpenAI%20Hackathon/.agent-worktrees/incident-m3-frontend/apps/web/app/incidents/%5Bid%5D/page.tsx) to fetch the investigation report in parallel with other sub-resources.
* Implemented visible Loading, 404 (not started yet), and Error states for the investigation.
* Designed the completed investigation view to render:
  * **Status & Remediation Gate Banners**: showing when status is `COMPLETE` and enabling/disabling downstream remediation.
  * **Incident Summary**: narrative details with click-to-focus citation links.
  * **Code Mapping**: listing affected files (`src/checkout.ts`, `src/checkout.test.ts`), suspect commit `c7f2e9a`, and the missing no-discount test gap with their citations.
  * **Ranked Hypotheses**: exactly three hypotheses displaying rank, confidence, concise rationale, supporting/contradicting citations, unknowns, and falsification check steps.
  * **Citation Scroll & Focus Links**: clicking any citation link in the report targets, expands, scrolls, and highlights the corresponding provenance card in the left telemetry column.
  * **Audit Log**: listing rejected claims showing citation checking.
  * **Safe Insufficient Evidence State**: renders a prominent warning panel displaying requested evidence and actions, and disables all remediation plans/approvals.

### 4. Extended Playwright Tests (`apps/web`)
* Extended the Playwright E2E flow in [golden-evidence.spec.ts](file:///D:/Work/Codex/Hackathon%20Projects/OpenAI%20Hackathon/.agent-worktrees/incident-m3-frontend/apps/web/e2e/golden-evidence.spec.ts) to assert the complete investigation report:
